I reviewed the metric, trace, and log analyses: many services/pods showed synchronized anomalies starting at Unix timestamp 1647790200 (2022-03-20 23:30:00 UTC+8). productcatalogservice pods exhibited very large container filesystem-read faults tied to node-6, many other services’ container KPIs referenced node-6, and node-level metrics showed elevated IO wait and load. These signals consistently indicate a node-level I/O hotspot on node-6 that propagated to multiple containers and services.

```json
{
    "1": {
        "root cause occurrence datetime": "2022-03-20 23:30:00",
        "root cause component": "node-6",
        "root cause reason": "node disk read I/O consumption"
    }
}
```
